@Node Description

	@{u}@{b}Short description of Searcher@{ub}@{uu}



Searcher is a really @{u}big@{uu} file finder, with many options :
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Search using index (faaaassst) and an index manager.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Support tooltypes and CLI arguments.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} File type with multi-selection (include and exclude)
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Date of creation.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Minimum and/or maximum size.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Auto stop.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Multi-include strings.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Multi-exclude strings.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Actions on finded files : copy, delete.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Multi-actions associated with every file format.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} List of finded files can be saved.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Lists can be mix.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Case sensitive.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} Diplay buffer.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} AppWindow.
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} And @{b}MANY@{ub} others...


Searcher is @{b}shareware@{ub} since 3.0. This version is not limited in any way, but if you like it, please support @{"The author" link Auteur} and consider to @{"register" link Register}.

@Endnode

@Node Installation "How install Searcher ?"

	@{u}@{b}Installation@{ub}@{uu}



Oh no ! No installer script ! Don't panic, it's easy.

Searcher.catalog and fileclass.prefs used by Searcher are different to previous version. So it is recommended to copy :
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}fileclass.prefs@{ui} in @{i}ENV:@{ui}
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}searcher.catalog@{ui} in @{i}LOCALE:catalogs/YourLanguage/@{ui}
 @{bg fill}   @{bg background} @{i}fileclassprefs.catalog@{ui} dans @{i}LOCALE:catalogs/YourLanguage/@{ui}

@Endnode

@Node Config "Requirement"

	@{u}@{b}Searcher need :@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg fill}   @{bg background} OS 2.1 ou greater.
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} The ReqTools.library © Nico François.

	@{u}@{b}Searcher use if present :@{ub}@{uu}

@{bg fill}   @{bg background} The @{i}FileClass.prefs@{ui} file (for file formats).
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} The @{i}locale.library@{ui} and the catalogs @{i}searcher.catalog@{ui}.
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} The little but useful command @{i}xPK@{ui} by Urban Dominik Müller (in @{i}c:@{ui}).
@{bg fill}   @{bg background} The CrunchPatch option of the powerful @{i}MCP@{ui} to have a total File Type ID of @{"compacted files" link Compact}.


Useful to know :
The revision of FileClassPrefs included in this package isn't compatible with the previous version. So, IconAct 1.0 can't work. If you use IconAct, you must have the last version.

Good to have : an hard disk, a clock (in the Amiga ;-)


@Endnode

@Node FenetreA "Main window"

	@{u}@{b}Description of the main window@{ub}@{uu}

 

@{b}The listview :@{ub} here appear the finded files. You can launch the associated utility of a file by clicking on it. The file format should appear in the @{i}Status@{ui} gadget.

@{b}Save the list :@{ub} you can save the list of finded files in an ASCII file. It only works if the list is'nt empty.

@{b}Path :@{ub} this is the path used by Searcher for the research. You can select a path by clicking on the @{i}Choose@{ui} gadget. It opens a ReqTools requester.

@{b}Key :@{ub} this is a key-word used for the research. You can use @{"wildcards" link Jokers} to enter 50 different strings.

@{b}Choose :@{ub} this gadget opens a ReqTools requester to select a path.

@{b}Options :@{ub} this gadget opens the @{"configuration window " link FileType} of Searcher.

@{b}Delete :@{ub} this gadget delete the selected file in the list, after having a confirmation. The name is also deleting from the list.

@{b}Copy :@{ub} this gadget copy the selected file in the list.

@{b}Go :@{ub} to start a search, if the selected path is valid.


@Endnode

@Node FenetreB "Configuration window"

	@{u}@{b}Configure Searcher@{ub}@{uu}

	 1.  @{"       File Type       " link FileType}
	 2.  @{"    File Date/Size     " link FileDate}
