	 4.  @{"        Display        " link Affichage}
	 5.  @{"      Limit/Index      " link Limite}


@Endnode

@Node FileType "File Type"

	@{u}@{b}Description of the filetypes options@{ub}@{uu}



@{b}Keyword :@{ub} this is a keyword used for the research. You can use @{"wildcards" link Jokers} to enter 50 different strings.

@{b}Leave out :@{ub} this is the opposite of the keyword. You can aslo use @{"wildcards" link Jokers} to enter 50 different strings.

@{b}Part of the name :@{ub} you can define characters as a part of the name of the file.

@{b}Exact name :@{ub} you can define characters as the exact name of the file.

@{b}Begin of the name :@{ub} you can define characters as the beginning of the name of the file.

@{b}end of the name :@{ub} you can define characters as the end the name of the file.

@{b}Use * :@{ub} you can define characters with the usage of the * @{"wildcard" link Jokers}.

@{b}Files :@{ub} research can be based on files.

@{b}Directories :@{ub} research can be based on directories.

@{b}Files and directories :@{ub} research can be based on files and directories.

@{b}Format :@{ub} this option use the @{i}FileClass.prefs@{ui} file and isn't valid for directories.
@{b}o@{ub}      : means that the format is disable.
@{b}+@{ub} ou @{b}-@{ub} : means that the format is enable. @{b}+@{ub} means that the file format must be one of the selected types (included). @{b}-@{ub} means that the file format can't be one of the selected types (excluded). The usage of this fonction slow the research.


@Endnode

@Node FileDate "Date of the file's creation and size"

	@{u}@{b}Description of the file date and size options@{ub}@{uu}



@{b}From :@{ub} enable/disable the minimum date of file's creation.

@{b}To :@{ub} enable/disable the maximum date of file's creation.

@{b}January... :@{ub} define the mounth of the date.

@{b}Day :@{ub} define the day of the date ;-)

@{b}Year :@{ub} define the year of the date ;-)

@{b}In the last X days :@{ub} to make a research on the files created in the last X days. The button enable/disable this option.


@{b}Minimum size :@{ub} this gadget enable/disable this option. The gadget on the right define the minimum size.

@{b}Maximum size :@{ub} this gadget enable/disable this option. The gadget on the right define the maximum size.

@{b}Bytes... :@{ub} define the unit of the minimum/maximum size.

Important : options on size are used by Searcher only for files.


@Endnode

@Node GeneralOptions "Options"

	@{u}@{b}Description of the general options@{ub}@{uu}



@{b}Ignore .info :@{ub} to ignore or not the @{i}.info@{ui} files (icons).

@{b}Alphabetic classifying :@{ub} enable/disable the alphabetic sort of the list at the end of the research.

@{b}Mash the previous list :@{ub} results of previous research can be conserved or not if a new research start.

@{b}Ignore directories :@{ub} scan or ignore the sub-directories in the root directory.

@{b}Case sensitive :@{ub} enable/disable the case sensitive in key-word and leave-word.

@{b}Automatic save :@{ub} enable/disable the automtix save of the list when the search is completed.


@{b}Password :@{ub} some files are crypted with XPK and need a password.


@Endnode

@Node Affichage "Display et automatic stop"

	@{u}@{b}Description of the buffer and the automatic stop@{ub}@{uu}



@{b}Use buffer :@{ub} The list can be refresh only if X news files have been finded. This option speed up the research if a lot of files are sorted.

@{b}Automatic stop :@{ub} Searcher stop the process when X files are finded.


@Endnode

@Node Limite "Internal limit and index"

	@{b}@{u}Description of the internal limit@{uu}@{ub}


@{b}Internal limit :@{ub} Searcher use an internal list to store all the finded files. Problem : a big list takes a lot of memory, and a short list couldn't be sufficient for many files. So, the user can edit the size of this list. If the size is changed, the current list will be automatically reset on the next research.

@{b}Default :@{ub} to restore the default value of the internal list size (200 files).



	@{b}@{u}Description of the index@{uu}@{ub}


@{b}Use index :@{ub} to use or not an index. If this option is enable, the @{i}Path@{ui} gadget is disable on the main window. Using an index is very fast.

@{b}Index file :@{ub} the name of the index file.

@{b}Choose an index file :@{ub} open a requester to choose an index file. If you choose an existant index file, the @{i}index path@{ui} appears in the gadget.

@{b}Index path :@{ub} the path used by the index.

@{b}Choose an index path :@{ub} open a requester to choose an index path.

@{b}Create index :@{ub} to create an index. If the @{i}index file@{ui} or the @{i}index path@{ui} is missing, a requester appears.


@Endnode

