@Node ToolTypes "Tooltypes and CLI arguments"

	@{b}Note@{ub}


If a tooltype is disable (with ()), a default value is used.




	@{b}Tooltypes and CLI arguments supported by Searcher@{ub}



@{b}PATH=@{ub} : the path of the search.

@{b}KEY=@{ub} : the key-word. @{"Wildcard" link Jokers} are available.

@{b}MODEKEY=@{ub} : specify the key mode. Supported arguments are : PART, EXACT, BEGIN, END, USE*.

@{b}LEAVE=@{ub} : the leave-word. @{"Wildcards" link Jokers} are available.

@{b}MODELEAVE=@{ub} : specify the leave mode. Supported arguments are : PART, EXACT, BEGIN, END, USE*.

@{b}TYPE=@{ub} : specify the search mode. Supported arguments are : FILES, DIRECTORIES, FILES&DIRECTORIES.

@{b}FILETYPEINCL=@{ub} : specify the filetypes. To use more than one filetype, simply use @{"Wildcards" link Jokers}. If the name of a filetype has a space, you must replace it by "_".

@{b}FILETYPEEXCL=@{ub} : specify the filetypes. To use more than one filetype, simply use @{"Wildcards" link Jokers}. If the name of a filetype has a space, you must replace it by "_".

@{b}FROM=@{ub} : the minimum date. Format is : dd/mm/yyyy.

@{b}TO=@{ub} : the maximum date. Format is : dd/mm/yyyy.

@{b}LASTDAYS=@{ub} : specify the number of days.

@{b}SIZEMIN=@{ub} : minimum size in bytes.

@{b}SIZEMAX=@{ub} : maximum size in bytes.

@{b}IGNOREINFO=@{ub} : enable or disable this option. Supported arguments are : YES, NO.

@{b}MASHLIST=@{ub} :  enable or disable this option. Supported arguments are : YES, NO.

@{b}IGNOREDIR=@{ub} :  enable or disable this option. Supported arguments are : YES, NO.

@{b}CASESENSITIVE=@{ub} : enable or disable this option. Supported arguments are : YES, NO.

@{b}AUTOSAVE=@{ub} : enable or disable this option. Supported arguments are : YES, NO.

@{b}PASSWORD=@{ub} : the XPK password.

@{b}BUFFER=@{ub} : specify the number of files used for the buffer.

@{b}AUTOSTOP=@{ub} : specify the number of files used for the automatic stop.

@{b}INTERNALLIMIT=@{ub} : specify the internal limit.

@{b}INDEX=@{ub} : specify the complet index file path to use.

@{b}INDEXPATH=@{ub} : specify the path used for index.

@{b}SAVEPATH=@{ub} : specify the path used for saved finded files list.

@Endnode
